@endnode
@node FEATURES "features"

@{b}Features@{ub}

- This software is FreeWare.
- Split/join selected files and directories.
- Hamming and CRC codes used for secure data encoding and decoding during
  join and split operations.
- Selectable output media size.
- Selectable working buffer.
- Selectable archiving base name.
- Wild cards supported (amiga + unix)

@endnode
@node REQUIREMENTS "requirements"

@{b}Requirements@{ub}

- Amiga :-)
- ixemul.library 48+
  (ftp.ninemoons.com/geekgadgets/amiga/m68k/snapshots/current/bin/ixemul-48.0-bin.tgz)

@endnode
@node INSTALLATION "installation"

@{b}Installation@{ub}

No special installation needed.
Just copy this program where you want.
@endnode
@node USAGE "usage"
@{b}Usage@{ub}

splitter [options] <file | directory  ...>

Options are:
 -h, --help          print help
 -j, --join          join (reverse action)
 -u, --update        update (write only newer files)
 -t, --test          only test (do not write any files)
 -l, --list          list files in the archive
 -o, --overwrite     overwrite existing files (do not ask)
 -n, --name S        base name of the 'huge' file      (default S=hugefile)
 -s, --hugesize N    size of the 'huge' file           (default N=730112)
 -b, --buffersize N  preferred size of memory buffer   (default N=30720)
 -v, --verbosity N   versity level 0 - 2               (default N=2)
 -c, --ignore-crc    ignore CRC                        (default No)
 -d, --ignore-date   do not set the date from archive  (default No)

You can also create a configuration file in your $HOME directory named .splitterrc and place your default values there.
Example configuration file can be found in the distribution. Modify it to suit your requirements.

Example usage:

splitter --name myarchive --hugesize 50000 foo.txt foodir

Creates archives called myarchive.xxx 50000 bytes each from file foo.txt and directory foodir

splitter --join --name myarchive

Creates original foo.txt and foodir from myarchive.xxx

@endnode
